Package net.egartley.beyondorigins.objects

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnimatedEntity
    An Entity with associated animations
    Animation
    Represents a collection of AnimationFrame objects, which can be used for animating a Sprite
    AnimationFrame
    A single frame within an Animation
    Entity
    An object or character that can rendered with a sprite and have a specific position
    GameState
    One of the game's "states" that has unique render and tick methods
    Map
    Represents a collection of "sectors" for a specific map, or "level"
    MapSector
    A "sector" of a map, which fills the entire window
    MapSectorDefinition
    A collection of map tiles used for defining a map sector
    MapTile
    A "tile" that is rendered within a map sector
    Sprite
    A row, or "strip", of individual frames of a specific entity or object
    SpriteSheet
    An image that contains multiple sprites, each represented by a row, or "strip" that is specified in the constructor
    StaticEntity
    An entity that cannot be animated
    SubGameState
    Represents a "sub", or lower level, state within another game state
